<abstract abstract-type="short" xml:lang="en"><p><![CDATA[The article presents a methodological and political criticism of the category "valence", widely used in Brazilian studies on communication and democracy. "Valence" operationalization is based on simplifications and mutilations of the very reality that it seeks to describe; and brings an implicit ideal of journalistic impartiality that is questionable.]]></p></abstract>
